- Use Shadcn UI components with proper composition and customization.
- Leverage Radix UI primitives for accessible interactive elements.
- Maintain consistent theming with global components and color tokens.
- Keep UI minimal, clean, and black-and-white for now.
- Follow consistent spacing and layout using Tailwind’s scale.
- Use Tailwind’s mobile-first responsive approach.
- Add dark mode support via Tailwind’s `dark:` variants.
- Ensure accessibility (WCAG guidelines) in all components.
- Style using modular and reusable Tailwind utility classes.
- Optimize component bundle size via dynamic loading and code-splitting.
- Avoid inline styles; use utility-first Tailwind CSS classes.
- Ensure adequate spacing, margins, and padding for all components.
- Maintain consistent use of border radius, shadows, and typography.
